{"name":"Mallet","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Jean-Yves, Adelard, Alain, Henri, Jacques, Leonce, Lucien, Monique, Philippe.","French: nickname from a diminutive of   Mal   ‘bad’. Alternatively, from a derivative of the related Old French word <i>maleit</i> ‘accursed’ (from Latin <i>maledictus</i>, the opposite of <i>benedictus</i> ‘blessed’), applied as a nickname for an unlucky person. Compare   Malet   1.","French: variant of   Malet   2, an Old French pet form of the personal name   Malo  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Mallatt","meanings":["English: variant of   Mallet  ."]},{"name":"Mallette","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Marcel, Andre, Donat, Emile, Francois, Jacques, Laurent, Pierre, Rolande.","Altered form of French   Mallet  , reflecting the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>. Compare   Mallett  .","English: rare variant of   Mallett  ."]},{"name":"Mal","meanings":["Slovenian: nickname for a physically small man, from <i>mal</i> ‘small, little’.","French (mainly Nord): nickname from <i>mal</i> ‘bad’ (from Latin <i>malus</i>).","Indian (northern states): variant of   Mall  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Mallet (1 Daughter) was born about 1445, in Chilham, Kent, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs William Mallet."},"et":{"about 1445–":"umbes 1445–Surnud","1447–Female":"1447–Surnud","1467–1564":"1467–1564","1445–Male":"1445–Surnud","1447":"1447","1467":"1467","1445":"1445","1564":"1564","about 1445":"umbes 1445","Chilham, Kent, England":"Chilham, Kent, England","Chilham, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Chilham, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1445–":"noin 1445–Kuollut","1447–Female":"1447–Kuollut","1467–1564":"1467–1564","1445–Male":"1445–Kuollut","1447":"1447","1467":"1467","1445":"1445","1564":"1564","about 1445":"noin 1445","Chilham, Kent, England":"Chilham, Kent, England","Chilham, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Chilham, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1445–":"environ 1445–Décédé","1447–Female":"1447–Décédée","1467–1564":"1467–1564","1445–Male":"1445–Décédé","1447":"1447","1467":"1467","1445":"1445","1564":"1564","about 1445":"environ 1445","Chilham, Kent, England":"Chilham, Kent, Angleterre","Chilham, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Chilham, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Mallet (1 Daughter) est né environ 1445, à Chilham, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mrs William Mallet."},"de":{"about 1445–":"um 1445–Verstorben","1447–Female":"1447–Verstorben","1467–1564":"1467–1564","1445–Male":"1445–Verstorben","1447":"1447","1467":"1467","1445":"1445","1564":"1564","about 1445":"um 1445","Chilham, Kent, England":"Chilham, Kent, England","Chilham, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Chilham, Kent, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"William Mallet (1 Daughter) wurde um 1445 in Chilham, Kent, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mit Mrs William Mallet mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"about 1445–":"about 1445–Desede","1447–Female":"1447–Desede","1467–1564":"1467–1564","1445–Male":"1445–Desed